==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*xlaupan''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[hlapa|hlāpa]], Old Saxon ''-hlōpan'' (Dutch [[loopen]]), Old High German [[hloufan]] (German [[laufen]] ‘run’), Old Norse [[hlaupa]] (Swedish [[löpa]]), Gothic [[𐌿𐍃𐌷𐌻𐌰𐌿𐍀𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈhlæːapan/}}

===Verb===
{{Unicode|'''hlēapan'''}} (class VII strong: ''3 singular present'' '''[[hliap|hlīap]]''', ''3 singular preterite'' '''[[hleop|hlēop]]''', ''preterite plural'' '''[[hleopon|hlēopon]]''', ''past participle'' '''[[hleapen|hlēapen]]''')
# to [[run]]
# to [[jump]], [[leap]]

